      • getMatchingText

        @Nullable
public String getMatchingText​(@NotNull
                              String pattern)
        Description copied from interface: SubstituteMenuItem
        Returns the text that corresponds to this action. Usually this method would return a fixed string, such as a concept alias (e.g. for for an action that inserts a ForLoop). Sometimes, however, it may be useful to base the matching text on the pattern. For example, in case of an action that inserts a method declaration, the method may specify that pattern foo corresponds to matching text foo().
        Specified by:
        getMatchingText in interface SubstituteMenuItem
        Overrides:
        getMatchingText in class DefaultSubstituteMenuItem
        Parameters:
        pattern - the text that the user has typed so far
        Returns:
        the text that matches this action, or null if not defined
